[Although there have been chikungunya cases before in Bangladesh, this
is the 1st ProMED-mail report. It reports outbreaks in previous years.
There have been outbreaks this month (November 2011) in northeastern
India (see ProMED-mail archive no. 20111117.3390), so it is not
surprising that cases are occurring in Bangladesh.

